location.full_address: Sri Adhigambatta Viswanathar Temple, Near Mounaswami Madam, Kumbakonam (Po.), Kumbakonam (Tk), Thanjavur (Dt)

deities.main_deity: Sri Aadhi kambatta Viswanathar Swamy (Form of Shiva)

cultural_info.special_features: Kambattam is the place where Cholas made coins

cultural_info.special_features: Lord Murugan is depicted with his footwear, Goddess Parvathi worshipped as a peacock

location.full_address: Meenatchi Sundareshwarar Temple, Arimalam, Pudukottai District

worship_info.timings: Morning – 06:00 a.m to 12:00 noon, Evening – 03:00 p.m to 08:30 p.m
worship_info.how_to_reach: Arimalam is 20 KM away from Pudukkottai, accessible via Pudukkottai–Aranthangi buses

cultural_info.historical_info: The temple's origin is linked to Chandran being cursed and seeking Shiva's blessing to regain his powers. 'Ari' means Chandran, 'Mazha' means Child. Chandran was positioned in Shiva's head and granted 'Shaaba Vimochanam'.
cultural_info.special_features: Sunlight falls on Shiva Lingam from March 19th to March 21st, Parents can symbolically adopt child to God to remove horoscope dosham, Believed to cure Chandran's curse

location.full_address: Sri Nadanapureeswarar Temple, Thandanthottam, Kumbakonam, Thanjavur District – 612202

worship_info.timings: Morning 09:00 A.M. to 10:30 Noon, Evening 05:00 P.M. to 07:00 P.M.
worship_info.how_to_reach: Located 11KM from Kumbakonam on Kumbakonam – Karaikkal road

cultural_info.historical_info: During the divine marriage of Shiva and Parvathi, Lord Shiva sent Agasthiya to the South to balance Earth's weight. He promised Agasthiya darshan in marriage form at this temple, blessing devotees with removal of marriage obstacles.
cultural_info.special_features: Dakshinamoorthy worshipped as 'Rasi Mandala Guru', Yellow clothes and chickpea garland offerings believed to relieve doshas of 12 Rasis

location.full_address: Arulmigu Vijayalaya Choleeshwarar Temple, Narthamalai, Pudukkottai District

worship_info.how_to_reach: Narthamalai is 18 KM away from Pudukkottai. Pudukkottai to Keeranur buses go via Narthamalai. Nearest station is Pudukkottai

cultural_info.historical_info: The temple was built approximately 1300 years ago, between 7 AD and 9 AD. It was initially constructed during the Pallava kingdom and later renovated by Vijayalaya Chola after defeating the Mutharaiyars. The temple is considered one of the first mountain cave temples built by the Cholas.
cultural_info.special_features: Round-shaped Garbagraha, Four-storeyed vimanam, Built following Vesara architecture, Stone inscriptions, Colorful paintings in Artha Mandapam

location.full_address: Sri Venkatachalapathi Swamy Temple, Oppiliappan Kovil, Thirunageswaram (Po.), Kumbakonam (Tk.), Thanjavur (Dt), PIN – 612 204

worship_info.timings: 6.00 am to 12.30 am - 4.00 pm to 9.00 pm

cultural_info.historical_info: According to 'Brummanda Purana', Markandeyan was worshipping Lord Vishnu and found a small girl (Goddess Sri Maha Lakshmi) under a Tulsi plant. Lord Vishnu asked to marry her, and promised to accept food without salt.
cultural_info.special_features: 13th among 108 Dhivya Desam, Celebrated as 'Vaikundam', Food offered without salt

location.full_address: Pachavanna perumal Temple, Kanchipuram, Kanchipuram District

worship_info.timings: 7.00 am to 10.30am - 5.00 pm to 7.30 pm
worship_info.how_to_reach: Near bus stand, walkable distance. Nearest major station is Chennai, then reach by road

cultural_info.historical_info: In old days, 'Thiruvattar' became 'Yadava Kuppam'. Sage Mareechi was an ardent devotee of Mahavishnu. Vishnu appeared in green disposition before the sage.
cultural_info.special_features: Main entrance faces south, Moolavar faces east, Not among 108 Dhivya Desams, Unique for appearing as two Perumals

location.full_address: Sri Pandava Thoothar Perumal Temple, Thirupadagam, Kanchipuram - 631 502

worship_info.timings: Morning 7:00 A.M. – 11:00 Noon, Evening 4:00 P.M. to 7:30 P.M.
worship_info.how_to_reach: 1 KM walking distance from Kanchipuram bus stand. No direct trains, nearest station is Chennai

cultural_info.historical_info: Approximately 2000 years old. Krishna went as a negotiator for Pandavas during Mahabharata. King Janamejayar performed penance here to see Krishna's Vishwaroopa Dharshan.
cultural_info.special_features: 49th among 108 Divya Desams, 25 feet high Krishna statue, Auspicious for people born in Rohini star

worship_info.timings: 6am to 12noon, 4pm to 9pm

cultural_info.festivals: Chithirai – Bramotsavam, Aani- Narasimhar Bramotsavam, Vaikunda Ekadasi
cultural_info.historical_info: A king called Sumathi was devoted to Lord Krishna. Krishna appeared in his dream and told him to build a temple at Bridharanyam (Thiruvallikeni). The idol has unique features like marks from Mahabharata war injuries.
cultural_info.special_features: Main idol appears with a moustache, Lord points to Krishna, Unique markings from Mahabharata war, 61st Divya Desam in 108

findmytemple_data.name: Pavalavalli Thayar Sametha Pavala Vannar Temple

location.full_address: Pavalavalli Thayar Sametha Pavala Vannar Temple, Kanchipuram, Kanchipuram(Dt)

worship_info.timings: 8.00 am to 10.00am - 5.00 pm to 7.30 pm
worship_info.how_to_reach: Located opposite Pachai Vannar Temple, walkable from Kanchipuram Bus terminus. No direct trains, nearest major station is Chennai

cultural_info.historical_info: During a conversation in Vaikundam, Goddess Lakshmi requested Lord Vishnu to change his dark complexion to golden by getting Lord Shiva's grace. The Lord worshipped Veerattakasar with 14,000 lotus flowers and was granted his wish.
cultural_info.special_features: Vimanam is in the form of 'Pravala Vimanam', Lord Vishnu appears in golden color instead of his usual dark complexion

location.full_address: Prasanna Venkatesa Perumal Temple, Tanjore, Tanjore District

cultural_info.special_features: Vaikuntha Ekadasi festival annually, 'Opening the gateway to heaven' (Sorgavasal) ceremony
